.TH agent-platform 1 "Agent Platform" "kingdom-monorepo" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
agent-platform \- load OpenAI-compatible agents, tools, and crews
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B python -m agents.platform.runner
.br
.B python - <<'PY' \n[script]\nPY
.SH DESCRIPTION
The agent platform ships 100 agents, 100 tools, and CrewAI-style crew definitions.
It builds OpenAI Chat Completions payloads locally without sending network traffic.
Use it to explore the registry, simulate crew kickoffs, and prepare tool definitions for downstream runtimes.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B load_default_platform()
Construct a platform instance pointing at the bundled JSON registries.
.TP
.B AgentPlatform.build_openai_chat_request(agent_id, prompt)
Return a dict containing the model name, chat messages, and tool schema list ready for OpenAI tool calling.
.TP
.B AgentPlatform.simulate_handshake(crew_id, objective)
Produce a deterministic kickoff plan that mirrors the crew playbook and handoff policy.
.SH FILES
.I agents/configs/agent_registry.json
.br
.I agents/configs/tool_registry.json
.br
.I agents/crews/crewai_configs.json
